 leading role in the industry. Centering pleasure and fun as legitimate policy goals, Weed Rules puts forth specific policies to advocate for a more just, sensible, and joyous post-legalization society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aDrug legalizationzUnited States. 0aMarijuanaxGovernment policyzUnited States. 0aMarijuanaxLaw and legislationzUnited States. 7aLAW / Drugs & the Law.2bisacsh  abest practices.  abooks on law.  acannabis activism.  acriminal justice.  adrug testing.  aequity.  agrowing pot.  alegalization.  alegislative.  alicensing.  alocal.  amarket.  apolicy changes marijuana.  arecreational use.  aregulation.  arestrictions.  ataxing.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2023 Englishz978311131914808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2023z9783111318226oZDB-23-DGC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079134140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520975255?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520975255423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520975255/original  a978-3-11-079134-1  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131914-8  EBOOK PACKAGE Law 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGCb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-UCY